4.13 OEAtomGetResidue 
 
   
const OEResidue&amp; OEAtomGetResidue(const OEAtomBase *atom)
    
This function is used to retrieve the  OEResidue  associated with an
 OEAtomBase .  The  OEResidue  class is used to store information
used in biopolymer processing,  e.g.  proteins and nucleic acids,
on a per-atom basis.  The residue properties of an atom may be set using the
 OEAtomSetResidue  function.

  

  
          
     
        
